		(at 118 114)
		(descr "Teensy 4.0, THT/socketed. Vendored from XenGi/teensy.pretty (MIT), LOCALLY MODIFIED: bottom-side pads 35-44 (Teensy pins 24-33) removed - unused on this design and they consume routing area under the socket. Pads 15-19 (short-end row: VBAT, VDD, GND, PROGRAM, ON_OFF) also removed 2026-07-22 - unused or duplicated by the long-edge VDD/GND pins, and they blocked routing. Remaining pads: 1-14, 20-34.")
